================================================================================
PLAN T011: STEAM LAUNCH PREPARATION & MASCOT SYSTEM EXPANSIONS
================================================================================

This document details the roadmap and architectural expansions required next
to transition the 3D Desktop Pet application from a verified, bug-free prototype 
to a feature-rich, commercially ready Steam release.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. STEAMWORKS SYSTEM PREPARATION (PRODUCTION CONFIGURATIONS)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To replace the default testing context (Spacewar App ID 480) with the actual 
production game configuration:
* App ID Replacements: Swap out `480` for the allocated developer App ID in:
  - `main.js` (`steamworks.init(YOUR_APP_ID)`)
  - `steam_appid.txt` (Write `YOUR_APP_ID` to the text file)
* Steam Cloud Setup: Configure cloud save synchronization path to target the 
  relative `assets/settings` file (handles window coordinates, scales, active 
  models/animations, click counts, etc.).
* Steam Overlay Rule: Configure launch parameters to disable the Steam overlay
  for transparent window safety, preventing overlay graphic hooks from drawing 
  solid black backgrounds.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. STEAM WORKSHOP INTEGRATION (COMMUNITY MODDING)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Expand custom mascot support to scan, display, and load user-generated 3D models 
subscribed to on Steam Workshop:
* Workshop Scan Loop: On startup, query the Steamworks API for list of subscribed 
  Workshop items (GLB/GLTF models).
* Dynamic Dropdown Population: Load Workshop directories alongside the local 
  `assets/` folder, adding community-created mascots to the settings panel 
  selection dropdown.
* Asset Resolution: Auto-convert downloaded Workshop paths to valid file URLs
  and route them directly into the GLTFLoader.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. INTERACTIVE MOODS & TAMAGOTCHI-STYLE CARE METERS (Friendship Loop)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Introduce persistent core needs to increase user engagement and encourage daily 
interaction with the companion:
* Need Variables: Store friendship score, hydration check count, hunger, and 
  energy levels in `assets/settings`.
* Activity Depletion: Deplete stats gradually over real-world time (saved on exit, 
  re-calculated on launch based on timestamp offsets).
* Needs-Based Animations: Swap default idle animations according to need states:
  - Default: Happy floating/breathing.
  - Low Energy (< 30): Sleepy/sitting pose.
  - Low Friendship (< 20): Sad/pouting pose.
* Petting Interaction: Track high-frequency back-and-forth cursor movement 
  over the mascot's collision proxy. Register as "petting" to restore affection 
  and play heart particle animations.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. DESKTOP GRAVITY ENGINE & BOUNDARY PHYSICS (Newtonian Mechanics)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Transform the mascot window container into an active physics participant in the 
user's screen space:
* Screen Boundaries: Constrain the Electron window coordinate bounds to track the 
  desktop dimensions.
* Gravity Pull: Apply a downward gravitational constant to pull the mascot to
  rest directly above the Windows taskbar or active folder frames.
* Cursor Flinging: Compute cursor velocity vectors during drag-and-drop. 
  When released, fling the pet window across the screen with bounce decay on 
  touching desktop edges.
* Flailing Animation: Trigger a dangling/airborne animation loop whenever the 
  pet is falling or thrown.
